<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<package xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/packaging/2015/06/nuspec.xsd">
  <metadata>
    <id>bartender</id>
    <version>1.0.0</version>
    <title>BarTender (Seagull Scientific) + Drivers by Seagull</title>
    <authors>Seagull Scientific</authors>
    <owners>internal</owners>
    <projectUrl>https://www.seagullscientific.com</projectUrl>
    <requireLicenseAcceptance>false</requireLicenseAcceptance>
    <description>
BarTender label design software (Seagull Scientific) with the Drivers by Seagull printer
driver package and the Japanese instruction manual, installed as an internal Chocolatey
package.

By installing this package you accept Seagull Scientific's End User License Agreement, which
is presented by the installer itself.

This package does NOT bundle the (large, licensed) Seagull installers - it is a thin
Chocolatey wrapper only. Before installing, place the following files on the target machine
under `%CHOCO_LOCAL_ASSETS%\Bartender\` (defaults to `C:\ChocoLocalAssets\Bartender` if the
CHOCO_LOCAL_ASSETS environment variable is not set):

  BarTender\BarTender_Label Design Software.exe
  Driver\BeeprtPrinter_2024.2.exe
  Manual\取扱説明書_Ver202505.pdf

See tools/chocolateyInstall.ps1 for the exact lookup logic and the /SkipDriver, /SkipManual
parameters to opt out of the optional components.

This package installs three components silently, in order:
1. BarTender ("BarTender_Label Design Software.exe"), using the classic InstallShield
   "/s /v\"/qn ADDLOCAL=...\"" silent syntax by default - confirmed working against the
   Seagull-provided installer. Pass /Modern to try Seagull's newer "FEATURE=" syntax instead
   (only documented for BarTender 2019+).
2. Drivers by Seagull printer driver files ("BeeprtPrinter_2024.2.exe") and, optionally,
   a specific printer driver via the Seagull Driver Wizard (DriverWizard.exe)
3. The instruction manual PDF (copied next to the BarTender installation for reference)

IMPORTANT - No public product key code (PKC) is embedded in this package. Supply your
own PKC (and any other install-time options) using --params, for example:

  choco install bartender --params "/PKC:xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx"
    </description>
    <tags>bartender seagull-scientific label-printing driver internal</tags>
  </metadata>
  <files>
    <file src="tools\**" target="tools" />
  </files>
</package>
